Date: Thu 19 Oct 2000
From: ProMED-mail
Source: Belapan news agency, Minsk 19 Oct 2000 1145 GMT [in Belarusian
via: BBC Monitoring [edited

Belarus: 30 hospitalized after eating meat from rabid cow
------------------------------------------------
About 30 people have been taken to hospital in Hantsavichy, Brest Region,
after eating meat from a rabid cow, Belapan news agency reported on 19
Oct 2000.
This was the first case of its kind in the Region. The farm where the
infected animal was slaughtered is under quarantine and all the
livestock, including domestic animals, are being vaccinated. Altogether
this year in Brest Region there have been over 30 cases of rabies
discovered in foxes, cows, cats and dogs, the highest number for 20
years. The reason is not only the cyclical nature of the disease but an
increasing number of foxes and wolves together with a virtual halt to
hunting.
*********
