Rabies - Belarus (Grodno Region)
---------------------------------
Valeriy Pogol'ko, the head of the special pathogen branch of the Grodno
Region Center of Hygiene and Epidemiology, said the [number of cases of
rabies in animals has been sharply increased in Grodno Region. At the
present time there are reasons to say a "common joint focus" of the animal
rabies has been formed in the Grodno area. The main carriers of
dangerous virus are foxes. 32 rabies foci have been registered in the
region. Shchuchin, Dyatlovo, Vronov, and Ostrovets districts are the
most unfavorable in this regard. From the lab investigation of 120 animals,
there were 64 confirmed rabies cases, among them 45 foxes.
V. Podol'ko also noted [that during the last 2 weeks 56 people have been
admitted
to medical [facilities for help regarding animal bites. This situation needs
adequate measures and activities to prevent the disease from spreading
among animals. First of all, a fox catch and immunization of the
domestic animals [would be indicated.
******
[3
Date: 24 Oct 2000
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Belorusskaya Delovaya gazeta on-line, in Russian, 23 Oct 2000,
<http://www.bdg.minsk.by/news-bulletin/index.htm>

Rabies  Belarus (Brest region)
--------------------------------------
27 people have been hospitalized after a contact with the meat of a rabid
cow in Gantsevichy district, Brest Region. At first in a kolkhoz
(collective farm) "Zarya" a cow which behaved strangely was killed.
After a couple of days one more cow in the herd was observed with a similar
behavior, and the veterinary service suspected rabies. An
expert confirmed the diagnosis. According to the press center of the
Ministry of Emergency Situations, the Gantsevichy district veterinary
service and the Brest Region Center of Hygiene and Epidemiology are
conducting preventive measures.
